{"title": "Dramatic Disappearing Display", "content": "This is the thing where, during a climactic Boss Battle or event in a video game, the game's display (showing Score, the Life Meter and such) vanishes away, leaving a completely unobstructed view of the game area. Presumably, something so awe-inspiring and theatrical is about to happen that it deserves the player's complete attention, as if it were a Cut Scene.\n\nBut also, technical limitations of 8-bit systems often prevented both the display and the large animated segments of the boss from being displayed simultaneously and the majority of these examples seem to be on 8-bit systems.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaticDisappearingDisplay", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LegacyOfTheWizard", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EnslavedOdysseyToTheWest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BatmanArkhamCity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaOcarinaOfTime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheLegendOfZeldaMajorasMask", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MetalGearSolid4GunsOfThePatriots", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GodOfWarIII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TouhouSuimusouImmaterialAndMissingPower", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BlazBlueContinuumShift", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MortalKombat9", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EternalChampions", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Halo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HalfLife2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AfraidOfMonsters", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/RedOrchestra", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FinalFantasyXI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FinalFantasyXIV", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LordOfTheRingsOnline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMarioWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DonkeyKong94", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Eversion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicTheHedgehog1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GargoylesQuest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Bug", "/pmwik